	   <a name=101345949887753></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101345949887753><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Divine Armor and how to use it</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122349><span id=Scholar>Melifaunt</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>36 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 11th 4:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fellow Clerics!<br><br>I have currently passed 15 seasons of healing and praying but am still grappling with how and when to use Divine Armor (the spell that gives 18 seconds of invulnerability).<br><br>Scenario: Group is in trouble, maybe pulled something tough while casters' mana was low, and now people are starting to die. Cleric has full health but low mana,so low that he can't cast any healing spells anymore. Cleric sits down to med while tanks yell &quot;Heal! Heal!&quot; in desperation. Tanks die bloody deaths, then casters start to get whacked. Cleric is hit and knows he can't take on the MOB he is facing, so he casts Divine Armor and takes a slow stroll to the zone line.<br><br>Group comes back one by one and begin to take stock, and realize that cleric didn't die. Sometimes they think that we wimped out on them, but I don't think we need to die a senseless death.<br><br>Any thoughts or opinions on the issue?<br><br>Boethius<br>Level 15 Cleric Mith Marr<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
